narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: By taking this course, I learnt basic knowledge of Discrete Math including Set, Graph, Tree and Counting number. Also, Prof. Smith introduced several basic proof methods in Mathmatics. During the office hours, I was inspired by his instruction ---- He  not only gave me hints on problems but also led me to explore how to have the idea and how to verify my ideas.

Set theory
Graphs
Trees
Minimum Spanning Tree and Its Algorithms
Permutations
Combinations
Graph theory the most, counting might be learned before.
Graphic, sets, binomial thereom
I learned a lot about discrete math and my logical thinking is improved a lot.

I improved my proof-writing skills, specifically with articulating my ideas in a reader-friendly way. I also got a bit better at counting, I was never great at combinatorics but I think I have a better idea of how to approach these types of problems now.
Proof writing, graphs, posets, trees, discrete sets
The graphic skills
To think questions in a mathematical way.
